====Usage notes====
Sense 1. To prepare a bed is usually ''to "make" the bed'', or {{qualifier|US|Southern}} to "spread" the bed, the verb spread probably having been developed from [[bedspread]].
Like many nouns denoting places where people spend time, {{term||bed}} requires no article after certain prepositions: hence {{term||in bed|lying in a bed}}, {{term||go to bed|get into a bed}}, and so on. The forms {{term||in a bed}}, etc. do exist, but tend to imply mere presence in the bed, without it being for the purpose of sleep.

